cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with predicting the 3D shape of a deformable surface from a single view, which is a problem in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. The paper also deals with geometric consistency, which could place it under cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Additionally, the paper uses synthetic renderings, which could suggest it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
